<TITLE> Ex-BNP lawmaker Sardar Sakhawat sued for extortion </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Narsingdi, June 4 (bdnews24.com) - A local businessman Monday sued former BNP lawmaker Sardar Shakhawat Hossain Bakul and 19 others for allegedly extorting Tk 1 lakh, a police official said. Mokhlesur Rahman, manager of a brickfield, Vanguard Syndicate, filed the case with Manohardi Police Station, the area's police chief Braza Govinda Dey said. According to case details, Shakhawat, who was a lawmaker from Narsingdi-4, demanded Tk 5 lakh from the businessman to run his business in 2001. After a hectic bargaining, Bakul agreed to settle for Tk 1 lakh. Shakhawat told bdnews24.com that it was a false case. bdnews2
